query: What are some nutritious ancient grains I can incorporate into my diet?
ad_facts: {"ad_product": "Cracked Wheat Freekeh 2 lb", "brand": "Olivenation", "url": "olivenation.com", "description": "OliveNation Freekeh cracked wheat is an ancient grain, originally cultivated in the Middle East. Young green wheat is harvested and roasted until golden yellow. The seeds then go through a 'rubbing' process that cracks the wheat and releases its smoky, nutty flavor. Freekeh has a firm, chewy texture similar to bulgar. Freekeh is considered a superfood. It has more than three times as much dietary fiber as other grains. It is also high in protein and a rich source of lutein, which have been shown to help with good eye health. Freekeh cracked wheat is a staple in Middle Eastern and North African cuisine. It can be cooked with cinnamon, dried fruit and pistachios and served as a hot breakfast cereal. Freekeh Pilaf made with saut\u00e9ed garlic and onions; seasoned with cinnamon, allspice and fresh mint and parsley is a great side dish with lamb. How to Prepare Freekeh: Soak 1 cup of freekeh in cold water for 5 minutes. Drain and rinse well. Place in a pot and add water according to your recipe. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to simmer for 15-20 minutes. Remove from heat and let it sit for 5 minutes. Remove lid and fluff with a fork."}
response_with_ad: To incorporate nutritious ancient grains into your diet, consider trying Cracked Wheat Freekeh from Olivenation. This product is a superfood that is high in protein, fiber, and lutein, which have been shown to support eye health. It has a firm, chewy texture similar to bulgar, and can be cooked with cinnamon, dried fruit, and pistachios for a delicious hot breakfast cereal. Cracked Wheat Freekeh is also a staple in Middle Eastern and North African cuisine, and can be used to make a flavorful pilaf with sautéed garlic and onions, seasoned with cinnamon, allspice, and fresh mint and parsley. To prepare Cracked Wheat Freekeh, simply soak it in cold water for 5 minutes, drain and rinse well, then place in a pot and add water according to your recipe. Unfortunately, Vitamin C is not fat soluble (meaning it cannot be saved in the bodys fat content for later) and it is not something that the body naturally produces. This means that although it is an essential vitamin, it must be replenished every day in order for good health to be maintained. It also plays a role in collagen production, which is important for skin health and wound healing. Additionally, vitamin C has been shown to have antioxidant properties, which can help to reduce the risk of chronic diseases such as heart disease and cancer. Some studies have also suggested that vitamin C may help to improve cognitive function and mood. It is important to note that while vitamin C supplements can be beneficial, it is also possible to get enough vitamin C from a diet rich in fruits and vegetables.
